I also got the chicken mole enchiladas. I'm not an expert on mole, but it was by far the best I've ever had. I am looking forward to coming back to this place again and again!

Pick up from during quarantine and we were really impressed. Everything tasted amazing and was still really hot. A welcome edition to the neighborhood.
Something different from the typical  mexican food.....very good.

Let me tell you, if you haven't gone here yet, you're missing out. Absolutely amazing food, great service and environment, and very proud Uptowners! Having roots from Oaxaca, I love coming to feel connected to my family culture, and the amazing food obviously helps! Pictured below is a stuffed acorn squash with mole and a tlacopan on the side. It's nice to have more underrepresented regional culture and cuisine to showcase the beauty of Mexico.

This place is so cute and tucked away and we are so happy we found it. We got lemonade and tamarind agua fresca which was fresh squeezed deliciousness. The salmon was phenomenal, vibrant and veg cooked to perfection. The skirt steak was so flavorful, tender, and perfectly cooked. The mole was interesting and a rare time I’ve been able to genuinely try something new. Wish I could give this more stars, will return soon with tequila (BYOB) and room for dessert!
This was my first time ordering with this restaurant; it’s right by my house, and I regret not going sooner! The tamales and guacamole are delicious! This will be a new go to!

I’ve only experienced their food delivery during these times, but even then it’s the best Mexican food I’ve ever had. The tamales wrapped in plantain leaves are amazing...I’ve had all of them and I have a favorite (Puerco en Mole Verde) , but they are all worth an accolade. Their guacamole is on point and the chips are fresh and killer. The chicken in the chicken taco is so tender and seasoned so perfectly that you don’t need the sauce on the side. I can’t wait to actually come visit the restaurant in person. Great job making amazing food.
Great food. I believe it's still byob

Without a doubt this is a hidden gem! This is a Mexican restaurant that features a South of Mexico style (Oaxaca). Food is fresh and so far it is the most authentic Mexican spot I have found in Chicago. Make sure to try the mole or the Quail. The Aguas Fresh as are actually fresh made (Not from powder). The place is a bit pricy but trust me... It's worth it!

Fresh, delicious seafood in a prime location. The atmosphere, decor and service are impeccable. What a great place offering fantastic food and drink! Terrific lunch! The staff is excellent and knowledgeable, the food was amazing. Try the crab linguini.

It's not an exaggeration to say that everything was delicious, beautifully presented, and the staff is so welcoming and patient with first-time guests. Our party of six started with tamales Oaxagueños (soft, spicy = A+), garnacha, and tlacoyos de frijoles - plenty for everyone to try, and they disappeared quickly! For entrees, three of us ordered the cornish hen in mole, and we also had the cod with pumpkin-seed sauce, tlayudas with spicy beef, and shrimp diablo. When this group stops talking because we can't stop eating, you KNOW the food is great! Already looking forward to our next visit.
Great Mexican place on the north side. Nicer than a taqueria but still comfortable and casual. Tried a variety of dishes, portions were large and everything was really good, especially the tamale.
I love this place. The food is fantastic!

Music was a bit loud so if you have a big table probably will have a hard time hearing someone on the other end.  There is metered street parking in front.  Staff was very friendly and quick. Definitely will go back.
Wonderful.

In the best way, this is not what you think of when an American says “Let’s go get Mexican food”  This place is 100% authentic food specifically from Oaxaca. If you want to try amazing Oaxacan cuisine, this is probably your best bet in the city of Chicago. The menu items change, the ambiance is warm and intimate, the food is VERY good.  I had a fire-grilled quail dish that I claimed to be “the best poultry I’ve had in years” - Go try this unique restaurant and stop by the other numerous family-owned businesses on the Argyle St. block!

Consistent and excellent. Always delicious food served and prepared by a welcoming staff. Especially good if you have someone in your life who loves eating grasshoppers (chapulines), but call ahead to make sure they're available!
Amazing food, great service! A truly one of a kind restaurant in a great uptown location! We will definitely be coming back soon!
So fantastic and a very kind, genuine owner. Romantic atmosphere and just everything I want to eat.

We love this restaurant. It is not typical "Mexican food" for the most part, but specialties of Oaxaca. I've not found many places that season and cook meat so well, and they have wonderful vegetarian dishes as well. I'll mention the quail and lamb chops but there are many other fabulous and unusual options. The service is good though as business improves it can get a little challenging. BYOB but if you bring tequila they have the glasses and mix. We've taken many guests and everyone raves about it.

Excellent service, excellent food. Many vegetarian options, which I really appreciate considering that most other Mexican restaurants don’t have much for vegetarians.

I've been here several times since it opened and find it delicious every time.  Authentic, fresh ingredients, interesting flavors, best horchata in the city.  Vegetarian friendly. Both brunch and dinner have terrific menus.  Makes for a nice change of pace from other Argyle-area spots. And if you're waiting in line at over-rated crowded TWEET, walk a few buildings south and try this great place!

But still had great flavor, and the sides were delicious as well. We had crickets for the appetizer, not for me, but had good seasoning on it.

Every meal I’ve had here has been nothing short of spectacular.

Great experience here.  The food is prepared wonderfully, packed with flavor and there are some rare items on the menu like beetles, quail and rabbit.  This place appears to be a family-run establishment. With that in mind, please don't go here, expecting highly polished service.  The pricing is fairly inexpensive for what you get.  This is definitely a place I will return to

Chicago has many Mexican places, but in my many years here I have never eaten tamales as delicious as those I had at Kie-Gol-Lanee. You are up for a treat. With different varieties, Oaxacan style wrapped in plantain leaves or the more common corn husk wrapped we all know, the masa and filling of these bundles of joy are superb. Soft and creamy, cheesy and flavorful. A total experience. Don't miss it.

Full disclosure, I worked with these guys for years at another restaurant and couldn't be more proud of them with this place. This is the kind of place that if I didn't know them and really want them to succeed, I wouldn't tell anyone about it keep the secret from spreading. The food is simply amazing, easily standing shoulder to shoulder with places 2 to 3 times the price in the West loop  Add in the fact that it's BYOB and you've got the best "impress your date with your hidden Chicago gem" place on the Northside. I feel like my enthusiasm for my experience there is going to come off as disingenuous advertising for friends now, no matter what I say so I'll just leave it at this ; you need to go here. Killer food, killer prices, laid back atmosphere.

Excellent meal, varied and intriguing menu, and friendly service. Besides tasty appetizers and salad, we had the camarones a la diabla (very tasty and spicy sauce) and the bacalao en hojas de platano. Both were generous portions, well-prepared, and delicious. The place was busy on a Saturday evening, but staff were very attentive. We got a table right away and at least three different people came to our table to check on us. Other diners seemed very content, and I'd be glad to try more items on the menu.

Came earlier on a Friday evening, seated immediately. Homemade tortilla chips served with what was sort of a black bean paste were a tasty start to the meal. Roommate ordered one carne asada taco and their enchiladas in mole, stating both were flavorful and generous in portion. I got the grilled quail with grilled vegetables, which was served with black beans, rice, and corn tortillas. Grilled to perfection and super tasty. Washed down nicely with what must have been a homemade horchata, since the taste was out of this world.  Menu is otherwise full of many unique items you'd never find at a "general" Mexican restaurant or taqueria that didn't specialize in Oaxacan cuisine like this one.  AND THE SERVICE, lest I forget. There must have been at least two other people besides our main server at our table all throughout dinner checking in on us and making sure we enjoyed everything. Excellent.  I will be back to try more Oaxacan specialties, and highly recommend this gem for a delightful alternative to the typical Mexican restaurants in the area. Go here!

The service was very slow. We went for brunch and the restaurant seemed empty, yet we were there for over 1.5 hours. The food "looked" great, but the biscuits were dry and it just tasted off. The whole experience was just awkward and drawn out. We won't be going back.
Excellent! Interesting menu and carefully prepared food with great quality ingredients. Try the crickets!

As a born Oaxacan I can say the food here is authentic, has the homestyle feel from the region, I recommend the Tlayudas and the tamales the most. I loved everything about this place, 100% recommend it for anyone looking for real authentic food from this Mexican region

We made reservations ahead just to make sure we got a table, made one on line but did not hear from them back so I called and made it over the phone. Once we got there the parking near by is 2 dollars an hour so not bad. We walked in and were seated right away, our friends got the wine and the staff got the glasses, and for the beer our waitress offered to chill it in the fridge.  So we ordered a bit of everything, Tostadas de ceviche de camaron, aweseme taste, Tlacoyos de frijoles, awesome texture and flavors,  Cielo Mar y tierra, very good meat was nice and soft, Camarones a la Diabla awesome sauce,   Tamales were good, and for dessert, Tres leches and flan both good.  In other words, the food was great and their service was awesome as well since not only one waitress came around to check on us but 3 so that took it up a notch. Will definitely come back.

Different than the usual taco/burrito Mexican restaurant. Main dishes are simple, unique, and good. Great place to go if you want a lot of good food without paying a lot.  All the cheese seems to be the soft unpasteurized fresca stuff. I don't mind it but be aware if you aren't into that

Just checked this place out for the first time. So glad we did, really nice to have a different style of Mexican cooking in the city. Staff was friendly and food was great.  Totally a hidden gem. We'll definitely visit again soon.

Just a short block from the Argyle red line stop. BYOB and stop by soon!

Awesome new place in Uptown! The service is great and the food is fantastic. I almost hate to tell people about this gem, but need to make sure they stay in business. We went for the brunch, which was awesome in every way, can't wait to come back for dinner.

Try this authentic gourmet Mexican cuisine. Recipes come from the southern state of Oaxaca. This menu will expose you to many dishes that are common delicacies. We had barbacoa de borrego and guisado de conejo . The barbacoa is a lamb stew, the meat came off the bone! The rabbit dish was very tasteful. Tortillas are HAND MADE! Worth the trip to check this place out!!!
